   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Girls in School</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Northern Region has markedly lower education and literacy rates than the rest of Ghana. While only 30% of people 15 years old or older haven&apos;t received an education, that figure raises to over 67% in the Northern Region, 75% for women. Through our Girls&apos; Clubs, we work to empower girls in school, encourage female teachers, and provide a safe space for girls to voice their gender-specific problems and receive the support they need to stay in school.</narrative>
  </description>
